From 30fc504b2f264ef4b2db6295dd628ed7ada8871a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Split <split@example.invalid>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 22:38:30 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 65/65] media: rockchip: rga: require feature superset

Plain-language impact:
Jobs are assigned only to RGA cores that support every requested feature.

Kernel details:
The old test accepted any overlap between requested feature bits and a core feature mask. Require (feature & data->feature) == feature.

Source: split from patches/cleanup-draft after docs/11-bsp-audit.md verification.
---
 drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_policy.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_policy.c b/drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_policy.c
index 5889d27..5dcde3e 100644
--- a/drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_policy.c
+++ b/drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_policy.c
@@ -354,7 +354,7 @@ int rga_job_assign(struct rga_job *job)
 		}
 
 		if (feature > 0) {
-			if (!(feature & data->feature)) {
+			if ((feature & data->feature) != feature) {
 				if (DEBUGGER_EN(MSG))
 					rga_job_log(job, "%s(%#x), break on feature\n",
 						rga_get_core_name(scheduler->core),
-- 
